    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Health Insurance in Zurich</h2>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-8">
          <p>
            Zurich has some of Switzerland's highest health insurance premiums, but also offers excellent healthcare facilities and services. Here's what you need to know:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md"><h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6">Why is Health Insurance Expensive in Zurich?</h3>
          <p>
            Health insurance premiums in Zurich are among the highest in Switzerland due to several factors:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>High Quality of Care:</strong> Zurich boasts world-class medical facilities and highly trained professionals.</li>
            <li><strong>Extensive Infrastructure:</strong> The canton has a well-developed healthcare system with numerous hospitals, clinics, and specialists.</li>
            <li><strong>Mandatory Basic Insurance:</strong> The Swiss system requires everyone to have basic health insurance, which covers a broad range of treatments.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            While the cost may seem high, it reflects the excellent standard of care and wide range of services available.
          </p></div>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6">Understanding Basic Health Insurance</h3>
            <p>
              In Switzerland, basic health insurance (Grundversicherung or assurance de base) is mandatory for all residents. This insurance covers a range of essential medical services, including:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Consultations with general practitioners and specialists</li>
              <li>Hospital stays (in a general ward)</li>
              <li>Prescribed medications</li>
              <li>Certain preventative care measures</li>
              <li>Treatment in case of illness or accident (if not covered by accident insurance through your employer)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              However, basic insurance has limitations. It typically doesn't cover dental care (except in cases of serious illness), alternative therapies, or private or semi-private hospital wards. For more comprehensive coverage, supplemental insurance (Zusatzversicherung or assurance compl√©mentaire) is available.
            </p>
          </div>
            <ConsultationModal />
          


        <!-- Insurance Providers -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
