        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">Other Essential Insurances</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          {/* Personal Liability Insurance */}
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Personal Liability Insurance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Personal liability insurance (Haftpflichtversicherung) is essential as it covers damages you may cause to other people or their property. This includes accidental damage in your home or injuries caused to others. Many landlords in Zurich require tenants to have liability insurance.
            </p>
          </div>

          {/* Household Contents Insurance */}
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Household Contents Insurance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Household contents insurance (Hausratversicherung) protects your belongings within your home against risks such as theft, fire, water damage, and natural events. It covers furniture, electronics, clothing, and other personal items.
            </p>
          </div>

          {/* Legal Protection Insurance */}
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Legal Protection Insurance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Legal protection insurance (Rechtsschutzversicherung) can cover legal costs in case of disputes, such as employment issues, contract disagreements, or property disputes. While not mandatory, it can provide peace of mind and financial protection against potential legal expenses.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

